    {
      "text": "Jeremy McGrath Supercross '98 is a racing video game developed by Atod (A&D) and Probe Entertainment and published by Acclaim Entertainment under their Acclaim Sports banner exclusively for PlayStation. It was licensed to use the name and likeness of Supercross champion Jeremy McGrath.\nThe game allows two-player racing via a split screen. Players can create their own custom bike and custom tracks, which can be saved to a memory card.",
